      "source_key": "jtwc_abpw|western_north_pacific_area|invest_90w",
      "content_hash": "4056ea81037795f2",
      "platform_summary": "6.4N 153.0E | winds 13-18 kt | 1002 mb | MEDIUM",
      "platform_location": "6.4N 153.0E",
      "wind": "13-18 kt",
      "risk_48h": null,
      "risk_7d": null,
      "next_update": null,
      "raw_text": "(1) THE AREA OF CONVECTION (INVEST 90W) PREVIOUSLY LOCATED NEAR \n5.7N 153.4E IS NOW LOCATED NEAR 6.4N 153.0E, APPROXIMATELY 89 NM \nSOUTHEAST OF CHUUK. ANIMATED ENHANCED INFRARED SATELLITE IMAGERY DEPICT \nA BROAD AREA OF CYCLONIC TURNING WITH DENSE FLARING CONVECTION OBSCURING \nTHE LOW LEVEL CENTER. THE POSITION IS BASED ON THE CENTROID OF THE \nOVERALL CIRCULATION AND PROMINENT MID-LEVEL FLOW. ENVIRONMENTAL ANALYSIS \nINDICATES 90W IS CURRENTLY IN A FAVORABLE ENVIRONMENT FOR DEVELOPMENT \nBEING CENTERED IN A LOWER POCKET (10-15 KT) OF VERTICAL WIND SHEAR, WARM \n(29-30 C) SEA SURFACE TEMPERATURES, AND A POINT SOURCE JUST EAST OF THE \nLOW-LEVEL CIRCULATION CENTER (LLCC) ASSISTING WITH MODERATE POLEWARD \nOUTFLOW. GLOBAL MODELS ARE IN GOOD AGREEMENT ON A WESTWARD TRACK WITH \nINTENSIFICATION OVER THE NEXT 24-48 HOURS. MAXIMUM SUSTAINED SURFACE \nWINDS ARE ESTIMATED AT 13 TO 18 KNOTS. MINIMUM SEA LEVEL PRESSURE IS \nESTIMATED TO BE NEAR 1002 MB. THE POTENTIAL FOR THE DEVELOPMENT OF A \nSIGNIFICANT TROPICAL CYCLONE WITHIN THE NEXT 24 HOURS REMAINS MEDIUM.",
      "metadata": {
        "basin_section": "WESTERN NORTH PACIFIC AREA (180 TO MALAY PENINSULA)",
        "invest_id": "90W",
        "lat": 6.4,
        "lon": 153.0,
        "wind_kt_min": 13,
        "wind_kt_max": 18,
        "pressure_mb": 1002,
        "development_phrase": "REMAINS",
        "development_level": "MEDIUM",
        "bulletin_issue_at": "2026-04-08T06:00:00+00:00"
      }
